The elevator is old and slow, even if we just wanted to go down one level.	The hallways made me feel like i was walking into a very old appartment buliding walls had smears of all kinds.	The lock on the entry door to the hotel was duct taped closed so that anyone could enter the building without a hotel key.	The property is older but reasonably clean, would have been fine if staff had dealt with these people.	On the first stay, when walking to my room down the drab, tattered carpet, scratched up hallway, I was very apprehensive of what the room would be like.